⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ \begin{proposition} ⦉

  ‖ Let $A ∈ 𝗦_{++}^d$. ⦉

  ‖ Then the map $f: 𝗦_{++}^d → 𝗦_{++}^d$ satisfying
    $f(A) = ∈verse{A}$ is an isotonic function mapping the (open)
    positive definite cone into itself.
